import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other Injuries')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Diseases')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cases')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other injuries, and diseases over time?')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['wounds'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['disease'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Disease Cases')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axvline(data['disease'].median(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['disease'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of disease cases?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
